FBIS4-38326 "drsov104_d_94012" FBIS-SOV-94-104 Daily Report 28 May 1994 Regional Affairs Curfew Introduced in Ingushetia; Minister Dismissed Curfew Introduced in Ingushetia; Minister Dismissed LD2805184794 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 1600 GMT 28 May 94 LD2805184794 Moscow Russian Television Network Russian BFN [From the "Vesti" program] [Text] The Ingushetian president decreed a curfew today on part of the republic. Ruslan Aushev's decree states that this has been done because of a sharp exacerbation of the situation. Eight Georgians working on Ingushetian territory were killed on 27 May. The president of Ingushetia has released Bashir Aushev, republican minister of internal affairs, of his post.
